AND: &
OR:  |
NOT: ~
XOR: ^

SHIFT LEFT:  <<
SHIFT RIGHT: >>

0001 << 3 = 1000
0010 >> 1 = 0001

1 << 3 = 1000
10 >> 1 = 01

a >> 1 (divide a by 2)
a << 1 (multiply by 2)

swap the value of two numbers &a and &b:
a ^= b; b ^= a; a ^= b;

see if a a number is odd or even
if ((a & 1) == 0) -> even

change between negative value and positive value:
~a + 1;

get the absolute value:
abs = (a >> 31) == 0 ? a : (~a + 1)
abs = ((a ^ a >> 31) - a >> 31)